Large language models (LLMs), such as Qwen (通义千問), are advanced artificial intelligent systems designed to understand and generate human-like text across a wide range of topics and languages.

These models are trained on vast amounts of text data from the internet and other sources to learn patterns in language and develop the ability to perform tasks such as answering questions、writing stories、creating code、and more.

Large language models can be used in various applications such as customer service、content creation、data analysis、and research.

They are a key part of the development of artificial general intelligences and are expected to play an important role in the future of technology and society.

